---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Other Projects',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="relative h-[70vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden -mt-[80px] pt-[80px]">
    <img 
      src="/portfolio/other_1.jpg" 
      alt="Other Projects Background" 
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover -z-10"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black/60 -z-10"></div>
    
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold text-white tracking-wide text-center font-heading drop-shadow-lg">
      Other Projects
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-10 font-heading border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 pb-4">
      Autonomous Rover
    </h2>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-heading">Role</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        The autonomous rover project was a challenge to design a rover from scratch that could autonomously follow a given track and grab a can of a specific color at the end of the track. I was the lead for a team of five who all contributed to the project and ultimately led to our team placing second out of 40 teams. As team lead, I delegated tasks, made critical decisions on the architecture of the rover, and helped with the overall rover design.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-16">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-heading">Rover Design</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        In order to follow the track, the rover has three infrared (IR) sensors to detect when it is over or off of the black line on the track. This data is fed into an Arduino that decides what action the rover is to take, and then the motors that control the two rear wheels are rotated independently to set the rover on a correct course. The end of the track is signaled by a thick black line, after which the rover activates a PixyCam to detect a can of a specific color and grabs the can after it is within range. I helped to design the main chassis of the rover in SolidWorks, which was then laser cut and assembled.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-10">
        <figure class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <img src="/portfolio/other_2.PNG" alt="Rover Design 1" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-3" />
          <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-center italic px-2">
            Full rover assembly in SolidWorks
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        
        <figure class="flex flex-col items-center">
          <img src="/portfolio/other_3.png" alt="Rover Design 2" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-3" />
          <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-center italic px-2">
            IR sensor placement on the bottom of the rover
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <figure class="flex flex-col items-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <img src="/portfolio/other_4.gif" alt="Rover Design Animation" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-3" />
        <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-center italic px-2">
          Claw mechanism actuation
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

<div class="mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 font-heading">Competition</h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        The final competition track has a black line which the rover must follow, and several cans of different colors placed at the end of the track, one of which must be selected and captured by the rover's claw mechanism. The rover that completes the track in the shortest amount of time wins the competition. Our team placed second in the final competition amongst 40 teams, after many design and code iterations.
      </p>

      <figure class="flex flex-col items-center max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-10">
        <video 
          src="/portfolio/other_5.mov" 
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-3"
          autoplay loop muted playsinline controls
        ></video>
        <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 text-center italic px-2">
          Practice competition track
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

<section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-900 rounded-2xl my-10 border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 mb-20">
    
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-heading mb-6">
      SolidWorks Falcon 9
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      After receiving my CSWA certification for SolidWorks, I decided to create SpaceX's Falcon 9 rocket to continue to learn the CAD software and to challenge myself. I created the full rocket assembly consisting of the Merlin Sea Level and Merlin Vacuum engines, the first and second stages, payload fairing, landing legs, grid fins, and other components.
    </p>

    <img 
      src="/portfolio/falcon9_1.png" 
      alt="Falcon 9 Full Assembly" 
      class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 mb-8" 
    />

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      
      <img src="/portfolio/falcon9_2.png" alt="Falcon 9 Detail 2" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />
      <img src="/portfolio/falcon9_3.png" alt="Falcon 9 Detail 3" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />
      
      <img src="/portfolio/merlin_engine.png" alt="Merlin Engine SL" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />
      <img src="/portfolio/merlin_engine_vacuum.png" alt="Merlin Engine Vacuum" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />

      <img src="/portfolio/falcon9_4.png" alt="Falcon 9 Detail 4" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />
      <img src="/portfolio/falcon9_5.png" alt="Falcon 9 Detail 5" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700" />
      
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
